  "name": "Arduino hot pad keyboard tracker",
  "summary": "**Conversation Overview**\n\nThe user requested Claude to create a note in Apple Notes for tracking an Arduino project idea. They wanted the note titled with a reference to a \"hot pad for Arduino\" for keeping track of hot keys, describing it as a \"little app project\" with hashtag ideas included in the title. Claude successfully created a comprehensive note titled \"Arduino Hotkey Pad Project #ideas\" that outlined the concept of building a custom hotkey/macro pad using Arduino hardware. The note included structured sections covering hardware components like Arduino Pro Micro and mechanical switches, potential features such as programmable key assignments and multi-layer support, software considerations including QMK firmware, and various use cases ranging from design tool shortcuts to streaming controls. This appears to be part of the user's project planning process for developing a custom input device.\n\n**Tool Knowledge**\n\nWhen using Apple Notes integration, the add_note tool requires both a \"name\" parameter for the title and a \"content\" parameter for the body text. The tool successfully created a structured note with detailed project planning content. The user's request for \"hashtag ideas\" in the title was interpreted as wanting \"#ideas\" included in the actual note title, which worked effectively with the tool's naming parameter. The content parameter accepted multi-line formatted text with headers, bullet points, and organized sections, allowing for comprehensive project documentation within the note structure.",
